<br>
I was wondering about the &quot;Smiles, Says 'Ahh'..&quot; spells doing it, since I'd been using them (except lifetaps) on the spirits we'd faced, all the way up until the princess.  That's why I was so confused.<br>
<br>
Monday night, Volker (SK) seemed to trigger 2 wipes, and then me last night.  It seemed too much of an SK pattern to be coincidence.<br>
<br>
Maybe it was our proximity to the quest mobs in the case of the princess?  Being further away before that fight might not have triggered them?<br>
<br>
Also, it was established that Ghrif was the first to get attacked.  We just wrote it off as him being the closest person agro'ed on the path of the mobs to me...<br>
<br>
Either way, I'm holding off on any of those spells on the 1st and 3rd Islands...I'll stick to Flutter and Grim Aura, and I'll test my 49 spells when I get them for &quot;Emote&quot; messages that may be similar triggers.<br>
<br>
Not sure how to do a &quot;scientific test&quot; of this matter, though, since Dueling itself will trigger them, and I'd hate to wipe a raid just to determine what spells FOR SURE are safe.<br>
<br>
I'm sure Col's right, though, with the targeting thing...someone could have accidentally targeted someone and cast a spell...Assist Keys are crucial.  *shrug*  Just wanna be safe, is all. <p>Rukog DethBryngr<BR>
